<L>__{interior roderick's apartment spa night}
<A>__{making ardent love.}
<C>__{countess}
<D>__{without you, my dearest, i might have died without ever knowing love. inexpressible love! god of nature! bitterness than which nothing is sweeter, sweetness than which nothing is more bitter. divine monster which can only be defined by paradoxes.}
<C>__{roderick}
<D>__{let me give a thousand kisses to that heavenly mouth which has told me that i am happy.}
<C>__{countess}
<D>__{as soon as i saw you loved me, i was pleased, and i gave you every opportunity to fall more in love with me, being certain that, for my part, i would never love you. but after our first kiss, i found that i had no power over myself. i did not know that one kiss could matter so much.}
<C>__{roderick }
<D>__{we then spent an hour in the most eloquent silence except that, from time to time, her ladyship cried out: "oh, my god. is it true i am not dreaming?"}
